    <stitle>2 SPEED AXLE SHIFT UNIT: EATON - AIR SHIFT SYSTEM</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>AIR SHIFT SYSTEM</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="0">
            <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
            <para>The basic system consists of:</para>
            <seqlist style="arabic">
                <item>
                    <para>A two-position manually operated air shifter valve.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>A quick release valve.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>An air shift unit.</para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
            <para>The system operates at reservoir tank air pressure.</para>
            <para>An ignition-controlled solenoid valve exhausts the system and down-shifts the axle when the ignition
                switch is turned off. The electrical circuit is protected by a circuit breaker.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
